[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(43) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Rejoiced.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—This verse is full of joy; but before the rejoicing comes the abundant offering of sacrifices.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Nehemiah 12:43",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Nehemiah 12:43",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "For God had made them rejoice with great joy — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "By restoring the holy city to such a secure condition, that they could praise the Lord there without disturbance or fear. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And the children rejoiced — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And their hosannas were not despised, but are recorded to their praise. All that share in public mercies ought to join in public thanksgivings. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "So that the joy of Jerusalem was heard even far off ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Either their loud voices and instruments were heard at a great distance, or the fame of it was spread far and near.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "12:27-43 All our cities, all our houses, must have holiness to the Lord written upon them. The believer should undertake nothing which he does not dedicate to the Lord. We are concerned to cleanse our hands, and purify our hearts, when any work for God is to pass through them. Those that would be employed to sanctify others, must sanctify themselves, and set themselves apart for God. To those who are sanctified, all their creature-comforts and enjoyments are made holy. The people greatly rejoiced. All that share in public mercies, ought to join in public thanksgivings.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
