  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Also that day they offered great sacrifices, and rejoiced,.... Or many sacrifices, as Ben Melech interprets it; and these perhaps of the larger sort of cattle, oxen; and which, at least many of them, being peace offerings, the people feasted on them, so that it was a festival day: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "for God had made them rejoice with great joy; on account of the wall being set up all around, and so were in greater safety from their enemies: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "the wives also and the children rejoiced; while the priests blew the trumpets, and the singers sung and played on their instruments, the women and children gave loud shouts for joy: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "so that the joy of Jerusalem was heard even afar off; as at the laying of the foundation of the temple, Ezra 3:13. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "so that the joy of Jerusalem was heard even afar off; as at the laying of the foundation of the temple, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Ezra 3:13",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
